{"answer":"Among BRCA (Bladder urothelial carcinoma) patients in the PanCancer Atlas who are alive, only one histological type met a minimal sample size (≥5 patients) for estimating CDH1 mutation frequency:

- Muscle invasive urothelial carcinoma (pT2 or above): 3.28% of alive BRCA patients had CDH1 mutations (122 patients in this group).

No additional histological types within alive BRCA patients had sufficient numbers to reliably compute a CDH1 mutation percentage, so only one (rather than three) histological type could be reported from the available data."}
